class MyPoint implements Hashable {
  int _x, _y;
  
  MyPoint(this._x, this._y);

  int hashCode() {
    int result = 17;
    result = 37 * result + _x.hashCode();
    result = 37 * result + _y.hashCode();
    return result;
  }

  String toString() => "Point(x=${_x}, y=${_y}) hash='${hashCode()}'";
}

void main() {
  MyPoint pointA = new MyPoint(1, 2);
  MyPoint pointB = new MyPoint(3, 4);
  MyPoint pointC = new MyPoint(4, 5);
  MyPoint pointD = new MyPoint(1, 2);

  HashSet<MyPoint> points = new HashSet<MyPoint>();
  points.add(pointA);
  points.add(pointB);
  points.add(pointC);
  points.add(pointD);
  
  points.forEach(print);
  
  assert(points.length == 3);
}
}}}
